HEADWORD: Heliolite
<hw>He"li*o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Helio-</ets> + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>A fossil coral of the genus <gen>Heliolites</gen>, having
twelve-rayed cells. It is found in the Silurian rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
